values:
I haven't written much is while, guess I just don't want people to know what's really going on, that I'm slowing losing my mind. One thing that's been going on for a few months is this ringing in my ears. More in my left then my right though the right decides to chime in or should I say ring in now and then just to keep me on my toes. The buzzing was getting bad at work after they banned all on-line radio stations, Pandora I miss you. I broke down and bought an ipod nano that streams constant music while I'm working so I don't go completely mad. At night it's really hard to go to sleep because of the constant noise which seems especially loud. What you can't hear it too?  

I went to a specialist (ears nose and throat guy) to have my ears checked out and my hearing tested, he told me I had the healthiest looking ears he had seen in weeks.  The hearing test was very comprehensive. They even put me in one of those rooms that close out all noise except what they hope you can hear. I've never been in one of those for a hearing test before. I remember hearing tests in school where you sit in an office or class room with head phones on and they ask you to raise your hand if you can hear something.  So this little room they put me in and I mean little closet, thank god for the window otherwise my claustrophobia would have kicked into high gear. As it was it was only a low level panic of oh my god this room is small how long do I have to sit in here. The test came back with good hearing except on the high tones in my left ear. Well damn I could have told them that I can't hear much over that ringing.  

The ENT guy told me I have Tinnitus and there's not much you can do about it but learn to live with it. From the sounds of it he's lived with his most his life. Oh great thanks. Normally it's brought on by a very loud noise that hurts your ears, the Tinnitus often goes away over time, mine has not gone away its been going strong for a good 2 months or more, I've kind of lost count or don't want to keep count. Only problem is I haven't had any loud noise incidents recently I haven't even been to a concert in a while. I mean Dahlia can scream pretty loud but don't think she can do actual damage. The other possibility is stress. Oh well um yeah that seems to be my problem. Too much stress! Can it stop now already?

Well the roller coaster ride has finished now to pick up the pieces. Things were getting a bit hectic last week, changing every hour so I didn't do any updates on where I was going or not going with my job since it was just going to change. The final fall out was the position my boss had created for me was approved and I qualified by the chin or my chinny chin chin. I don't have a masters degree so we had to write up a very elaborate resume that showed I had qualifying experience. The final outcome was I had to give up reinstatement rights as an Administrative Assistant II. See there was this other job that came up last week that I could have transferred to but I didn't want to if I was able to qualify for the new job. But when you are laid off and they call you and say we have a job. If you say no, that's it your off the reinstatement list. I and hoped that if the new job didn't work out I would be able to go back to being an Admin II. No such luck and on top of that I am now in a position that is exempt. This is good and bad. The good is I can't be bumped, the bad is it's an at will position so if my boss decided to cut it for budget reasons I'm out with no job I could bounce to.  

During all this I was training my replacement from the Port. She is actually a nice lady and I don't hold anything against her for everything that happened. She's pretty happy I'm still around so she can ask me questions as things come up.

On Monday September 21st I started my new position as Management Intern. Yeah Intern is an odd title but the City does not see it as a temporary position. It's seen as a management training position. Oh God you know what this means don't you? I'm being trained to go into management. My new direct supervisor is great. She's all about making a path to where I want to be in 5 years and making sure I get everything I need to get there. It's a bit scary to say the least and I kind of feel I have been throw in the deep end with the sharks. It's sink or swim time.

I'm not going to lose my job. Why, oh why, do Unions and City politics have to make it so difficult and put you on this roller coaster that if your on the bottom of the list there is a chance you will get bumped/laid off. Which I'm not after all. Thank you. I know my boss was pulling every string she could. She didn't want to lose me. She is a bit of a strong personality, I like her a lot but I know people who don't want work for her. So for now I have a job to come back too. I'm taking a week vacation to go camp in the great out doors. Dahlia's first camping trip. Wish us luck. She is all ready she has her water bottle and everything.

I'm on it again. It's a bit stressful and not at all fun like a roller coaster should be. Things are made even a bit worse that M got laid off June 1st. He was hit by a Mack truck while we were watching my possible layoff train in the distance. It was a bit unexpected but in this economy there is not much you can expect except more layoffs it seems. So tomorrow night is a big budget meeting with City Council, lets not even discuss what the governator is not doing to the States budget that will affect the City's budget and the City will have to do another budget mid year.  After the 3pm meeting tomorrow and I have no idea how late it will go they are going to start sending out the layoff letters Wednesday. 

M and I leave for our camping trip to Yosemite on Sunday so I should know if I have a job to come back to or not. If I get a letter my last day will be July 3rd. So basically I'll be off a week of vacation and come back and have a week to clean up my desk and get everything ready for someone to come in and take over. It's a bit depressing. I'm looking at the side that I will be laid off and I will get a letter that way if I do I'm not shell shocked and if I don't I'll have a happy day.

OOh #5

I really hope we get to go. We have a site reserved and I really should start getting some of the equipment we are going to need just in case.

I don't talk to my sister (Tamara) much, she's busy, has 5 kids and is not very connected to technology, lives in San Diego, need I go on. Since having my own baby she has reached out a bit more. I think because now that I have a little one we have something in common. Also her youngest is only 3 months older then Dahlia. I wanted to share this. T sent this to me today on my cell phone. It makes me smile I may not talk to her much but it's nice when she sends a pic on the phone. She calls this Baby Yoga. ahhhh

1. Drove an 18 wheeler dry cement powder truck from the cement plant in Victorville to Lake Havasue City when I was 11 years old (sitting on my dad's lap)

2. Hiked the backside of Half Dome for my 21st birthday and had a bottle of wine and played frisbee on top.

3. Been hit by a Ford Explorer while on my motorcycle and now only have 9 toes. 
   (it doesn't say it has to be good things you've done)

It's a bit over whelming. We're home and I'm going to try and sleep now;) Expect to see lots of sappy posts from me about my beautiful daughter. Of course I couldn't have done it without he was really great though out the whole birth and everything.

But I'm still not a mom. Martins Parents came down and we had a wonderful picnic in the back yard. I seem to be in pretty bad shape first thing in the morning and late a night. During the middle of the day I don't feel too bad. I mean I'm uncomfortable but not in large amounts of pain. Martin grilled hamburgers on our BBQ and Helga brought German potato salad and fruit salad. It was all very yummy. I really do like spending time in our back yard. I hope we get to do it more often. So long as I sit under the umbrella and don't get another sunburn. Then Helga and I went for a little walk in the cemetery while Martin and his dad cleaned up. It was a busy day next door. I guess lots of people go visit their mom's on mothers day. Made me kind of sad because on fathers day I don't have anyplace to go to visit my dad since he was sprinkled into the Colorado River. Cemeteries really are more for the living then the dead.

The number one question everyone seems to want to know after if I've had the baby yet is have we picked a name. I'm a little sick of this question and a few people have upset me by their response to the names I tell them we are considering. Here is a little advice, don't bad mouth a name to someone who is pregnant obviously this person has put a lot of thought into the names they like and your not the one who's carrying/birthing the baby. I'm sick of explaining and defending why I like the names I've picked and sick of hearing why other people don't like the names I've picked. My cousin called and she made me feel a lot better about the whole thing. Had me laughing pretty hard. We are kids of the 70's so we missed the flower child naming our parents could have inflicted on us. She more so then I since her mom was more of the 60's peace, love then my mom was. The question is what will our kids think of us when they are older about their names. As she put it she named her kid after a vegetable (Kale) my sister Tamara likes Celtic names and just named her daughter (Anwen) and I want to name my daughter after a flower. All of us are trying to find names that are unique and special. Everyone has different reasons for the names they pick. I have questioned my choices and reasoning and have under pressure from others considered not using one of the names we have currently on the short list. Let me just outline the names why I like them, their meaning, and some of the different negative things people have said about them. May I also say thank you to those people who said positive things about the names and kept any negative comments to themselves. Iris or Irisa (one of my favorite flowers) I like it because it's short and simple and if my daughter asked me why I named her Iris I could say because it's my favorite flower and I think it's really pretty like her. It is of Greek origin, and its meaning is "rainbow". In Mythology: Iris was a messenger-goddess who rode rainbows between heaven and earth to deliver messages from Olympus. So far I've had people tell me it sounds like an old ladies name, or that someone they know used it as their kids middle name and they didn't like it. Dahlia (another of my favorite flowers) The girl's name Dahlia \da(h)-lia\ pronounced DAL-yah. It is of Swedish and Scandinavian origin, and its meaning is "valley". Also the flower named for 18th-century Swedish botanist Anders Dahl. This one doesn't have a Mythology connection like the other but I could give my daughter the same answer that it was my favorite flower and I thought it was pretty. The most common dislike of this one seems to be people say the child will be called dolly as a nickname. Other people point out the famous unsolved murder case of the Black Dahlia and think that would be a horrible name for my daughter. M says he wants to keep the options open in case other names come up where I think I'm a little stuck on one of these. There were other flowers I liked for names but they have been taken off the list for some reason or another so don't really want to try and mess with our past reasons why we crossed them off. Our plan as of now is to go to the hospital with these names and hope one fits her better then the other.

Since I have this big belly and yes I still have it. As of noon on Sunday my Due date I'm still preggers I've been having fun getting it painted. I wanted to try and get a cast done but sort of ran out of time looking for someone who could do it. So don't think it will happen. My friend Tami who is a model sent a present to my shower which was her friend who painted belly's so this was my first paint job. By Alana Dill Then since I have a very talented friend I got a custom henna done as well. Of course um it was a nice sunny day and we were enjoying ourselves out side while my henna dried and she applied the lemon and sugar and now I have a big red sun burned belly. I'll have to get a picture of it, or maybe not, not sure I want to remember the sun burn;) I'm kind of hopping I'm a few days late so this sunburn fades because it hurts right now.

It's really hard for me to be home from work and not doing anything. Though I forced myself to stay in bed this morning (after visiting the bathroom of course) I seem to be waiting for the inevitable, but patience has never been one of my virtues. I wish I knew when I was going to go into labor. I keep checking for the signs and even if have one that still could mean it could happen soon or a week from now. Since every woman is different they really can't tell you if this happens then you have 12 hours until contractions start or something like that. 

I get tired easy; I did some laundry and boy that wore me out. Thought I'd go for a walk. It seemed to take forever since I'm walking really slowly. Visited Piedmont grocery store and the post office and really it's not that far of a trip but I wasn't sure I was going to make it back home. I check my e-mail a lot and get board often so a few messages would be nice from people for me to keep my sanity. I read live journal but it doesn't change much. We'll see how I do this weekend, if I still haven't gone into labor come Monday I might be going stir crazy you can expect a post a day or more.
